Thought rationale notes (these rationale notes are for internal reviewers only and can be toggled off for final report).
Input: Findings from Pattern Detection, Taint Analysis, Sanitizer Recognition
Output: Human-readable report (Markdown), JSON findings file, and remediation patches/suggested diffs
Behavior: Organize findings by severity and file; for each finding include:
file path, line range
code snippet (with context)
taint path summary
why it's vulnerable
suggested fixed code snippet (one-liner and larger fix)
confidence score
Prompts:
CREATE prompt: "Create a structured report of SQLi risks found in this codebase, prioritized by severity, with clear remediation steps and code replacements."
Chain-of-Thought: "Sort High severity issues first, include a brief reproduction example when possible, and provide exact code edits (diff-style) to fix."
